== the numbered list prints every entry ==
    1  echo one
    2  ls
    3  cd /tmp
    4  git status
== a trailing count prints only the most recent entries ==
    3  cd /tmp
    4  git status
== a non-numeric count is rejected without printing the list ==
shit: 1:9: error: Builtin 'history': 'foo' is not a valid count.
     1 |  history foo; echo "rc=$?"
       |          ^~~ here.
rc=2
== a count past the list size still prints every entry, no overflow ==
    1  echo one
    2  ls
    3  cd /tmp
    4  git status
== the print flag echoes its operands and stores nothing ==
alpha
beta
== builtin history -a no longer reports an unknown builtin ==
continued
== type reports the builtin ==
history is a shell builtin
== clear empties the list ==
cleared
